change her name.

10:34.101 --> 10:36.301
So, I can't be
an educated, career-minded,

10:36.303 --> 10:38.003
self-respecting woman
if I take my husband's name?

10:38.005 --> 10:41.573
Shaming other women doesn't
sound very feminist, Mom.

10:41.575 --> 10:42.607
Mnh-mnh.
It doesn't.

10:42.609 --> 10:44.175
That is not
what I meant.
Oh.

10:44.177 --> 10:48.613
Feminism is
about women having choices.

10:48.615 --> 10:51.182
And obviously,
there is a right choice.

10:51.184 --> 10:54.452
Yes... taking
your husband's name.

10:54.454 --> 10:55.687
[ Sighs ]
Zoey: Wait.

10:55.689 --> 10:56.788
So, when we get married,

10:56.790 --> 10:58.289
you don't want us
to be Johnsons anymore?

10:58.291 --> 11:01.259
So, you're trusting Jack and
Junior to carry on your lineage?

11:01.261 --> 11:02.694
<i>That</i> feels right to you?

11:02.696 --> 11:04.763
<i>Diane nailed it.</i>

11:04.765 --> 11:06.665
<i>That did not feel right to me.</i>

11:06.667 --> 11:10.201
<i>But luckily, there was still</i>
<i>a move I could make.</i>

11:10.203 --> 11:13.938
♪♪

11:13.940 --> 11:15.206
Hmm...

11:15.208 --> 11:17.008
♪♪

11:17.010 --> 11:20.111
Okay, how we gonna make
this wedding about us?

11:20.113 --> 11:21.646
Can it involve my food allergy?

11:21.648 --> 11:24.449
Because I've been itching
to try out this new EpiPen.

11:24.451 --> 11:26.217
No. And is this
a joke to you?

11:26.219 --> 11:27.786
No.

11:27.788 --> 11:30.121
But what
are we gonna do?
[<i> Tablet warbles</i> ]

11:30.123 --> 11:32.123
Are we just going to be guests?

11:32.125 --> 11:34.392
[ Gasps ] Or worse...

11:34.394 --> 11:35.360
ushers?

11:35.362 --> 11:36.361
No.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.163
I refuse to be a nobody

11:38.165 --> 11:39.698
like some random cousin
or Junior.

11:39.700 --> 11:42.667
Together, we'll figure out a way
to make this wedding about us.

11:42.669 --> 11:45.070
"Together" like you and me,

11:45.072 --> 11:47.138
or the "together"
where you do all the work?

11:47.140 --> 11:48.707
The one where I do
all the work.

11:48.709 --> 11:50.408
I think that's best
for all involved.

11:50.410 --> 11:50.910
♪♪

11:55.148 --> 11:56.815
Hey, pals.

11:56.817 --> 11:58.316
Peep my new wedding suit.

11:58.318 --> 12:00.485
You look stupid.
Sorry.

12:00.487 --> 12:02.654
Aww, that's sweet of you Donna,

12:02.656 --> 12:04.255
but I'm used to it.

12:04.257 --> 12:06.591
No, no.
We're<i> playing</i> "Sorry!"

12:06.593 --> 12:09.394
Ohh.
Not to toot my own horn...

12:09.396 --> 12:12.097
Toot-toot...
but I'm really good at games.

12:12.099 --> 12:13.765
Because he has no friends.

12:13.767 --> 12:15.667
I once saw him play
an entire game

12:15.669 --> 12:17.435
of Movie Quiz by himself.

12:17.437 --> 12:19.871
Robin Williams.
Jungle in the house.

12:19.873 --> 12:21.873
Your favorite movie.
[gasps] Uh...

12:21.875 --> 12:24.075
[<i> Buzzer</i> ]

12:24.077 --> 12:26.745
Ah, "Jumanji."

12:26.747 --> 12:28.346
I was right there.

12:28.348 --> 12:29.681
I eventually won.

12:29.683 --> 12:32.250
Hey, listen, listen.

12:32.252 --> 12:33.351
I've been thinking.

12:33.353 --> 12:35.520
And we're about to be family.

12:35.522 --> 12:36.788
Mm.

12:36.790 --> 12:39.390
And I feel like
"Deaconess" is so impersonal.

12:39.392 --> 12:41.559
So how about
you just call me...

12:41.561 --> 12:43.428
Ruby...

12:43.430 --> 12:45.864
Johnson...

12:45.866 --> 12:47.799
Mrs. Ruby Johnson.

12:49.402 --> 12:50.468
Uh...
[ Sighs ]

12:50.470 --> 12:51.936
Mrs. Johnson.

12:51.938 --> 12:54.873
Okay, Mrs. Johnson.

12:54.875 --> 12:57.776
Now isn't that better?
[ Chuckles ]

12:57.778 --> 12:58.810
Okay, so...

13:01.648 --> 13:03.281
Martina Navratilova.

13:03.283 --> 13:04.783
What about her?

13:04.785 --> 13:06.451
Billie Jean King.

13:07.788 --> 13:09.420
Are you just naming lesbians?

13:09.422 --> 13:11.723
Oh, are those lesbians?
I had no idea.

13:11.725 --> 13:13.391
Ellen Degeneres.

13:13.393 --> 13:15.059
Hey, Grandma.
Huh?

13:15.061 --> 13:16.828
Can we go do something
other than this?

13:16.830 --> 13:17.896
Oh, yeah.
All right.

13:17.898 --> 13:19.497
I'll be right back.
Be right back.

13:19.499 --> 13:21.299
♪♪

13:21.301 --> 13:23.434
All right, everybody.
Dinner's served!

13:23.436 --> 13:25.970
All right. Hold on.
Hold on.

13:25.972 --> 13:28.439
Before we dig in, can we have
your attention please?

13:28.441 --> 13:30.742
Rhonda has come up
with a great way

13:30.744 --> 13:32.577
to celebrate
her and Sharon's union...

13:32.579 --> 13:34.279
all her idea.

13:34.281 --> 13:35.980
Mm.
Had nothing
to do with me.

13:35.982 --> 13:36.981
Rhonda, take it away.

13:38.351 --> 13:40.618
Baby, you know
you're the love of my life,

13:40.620 --> 13:42.253
and I cannot wait to marry you.

13:42.255 --> 13:44.589
So will you please do me
the honor

13:44.591 --> 13:46.591
of taking my last name
and becoming a Johnson?

13:46.593 --> 13:48.293
[ Chuckles ] Yes.

13:48.295 --> 13:49.360
- Yes? Yes?
- Yes!

13:49.362 --> 13:51.029
[ Laughing ]
Yes!
Dre: Wow.

13:51.031 --> 13:53.598
So easy.

13:53.600 --> 13:55.834
What kind of monster
did I marry?

13:55.836 --> 13:57.202
I can't believe this.

13:57.204 --> 13:59.537
So, wait.
Uh, you're giving up Duckworth?

13:59.539 --> 14:00.672
You can't do that.

14:00.674 --> 14:02.707
No, how we gonna play
"Duck, Duck, Worth"

14:02.709 --> 14:04.008
if you're not a Duckworth?

14:04.010 --> 14:06.144
Yeah, yeah.
H-Hold on. Hold on.

14:06.146 --> 14:09.380
You have been sharing Duckworth
your entire life.

14:09.382 --> 14:12.517
A-Are you... Are you sure
that you just want

14:12.519 --> 14:14.819
to just give up
your identity like that?

14:14.821 --> 14:16.120
What are you doing, Bow?

14:16.122 --> 14:18.456
Oh, it's just that Duckworth is
such a strong

14:18.458 --> 14:21.159
and distinctive,
distinctive name.

14:21.161 --> 14:22.994
So is Johnson.
Mm.

14:22.996 --> 14:24.729
All right,
we've had two presidents.
Mm-hmm.

14:24.731 --> 14:26.297
We have Earvin "Magic."

14:26.299 --> 14:29.534
We have
Dwayne "The Rock."
Mm-hmm.

14:29.536 --> 14:31.669
But there is a lot wrong
with Johnson.
What?

14:31.671 --> 14:34.339
You can never name
a kid Peter or Willie.

14:34.341 --> 14:36.341
Or Harry or Hugh.

14:36.343 --> 14:37.876
It's a really long list.

14:37.878 --> 14:39.878
It's a long list.
Now, Sharon...
Mm.

14:39.880 --> 14:43.314
Are you really sure

14:43.316 --> 14:47.218
that this is what<i> you</i> want?

14:47.220 --> 14:50.221
I don't know.
I mean, it seemed really sweet.

14:50.223 --> 14:51.556
Now I'm not sure.

14:51.558 --> 14:52.690
Okay, now, hold up now.

14:52.692 --> 14:54.092
15 seconds ago,
you said you were down

14:54.094 --> 14:55.693
with being a Johnson,
and now you're not so sure?

14:55.695 --> 14:57.595
Better you find out now

14:57.597 --> 14:59.664
than 17 years from now.
What?

14:59.666 --> 15:00.665
Uh-huh.

15:00.667 --> 15:03.501
Everybody,
my wife cuckolded me.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.603
That's not even
what that means, Dre.
But it's what you did.

15:05.605 --> 15:07.205
No, no, I didn't.
No!
Yes.

15:07.207 --> 15:09.107
You didn't take my name so we
don't have the same last name!

15:09.109 --> 15:11.342
I<i> have</i> the same name!
We started with the same name!

15:11.344 --> 15:13.378
I'm sorry,
but you just put me on the spot.

15:13.380 --> 15:15.580
Y-You know what, Sharon?
Take it from me...

15:15.582 --> 15:19.083
It's very important
that the entire family have

15:19.085 --> 15:21.519
the same last name.
It's not, though.

15:21.521 --> 15:23.588
Well, then maybe,
you know, Rhonda should
become a Duckworth.

15:23.590 --> 15:25.390
Ooh, shots fired.

15:25.392 --> 15:26.958
Well, the way I see it,

15:26.960 --> 15:28.360
there's only one way
to settle this.

15:30.096 --> 15:31.195
All right.

15:31.197 --> 15:33.932
Duckworths versus the Johnsons.

15:33.934 --> 15:35.133
Winner gets the name.

15:39.306 --> 15:40.939
Here are the rules.
Single elimination.

15:40.941 --> 15:42.607
That's all you need
to know.
Donna:
Let's get it on!

15:42.609 --> 15:45.576
[ Duck call honks ]
♪ DJ Khaled! ♪

15:45.578 --> 15:47.612
♪ Hey! ♪
♪ Yeah! ♪

15:47.614 --> 15:48.713
♪ We the best! ♪

15:48.715 --> 15:51.049
All I do is win, win, win
no matter what

15:51.051 --> 15:52.884
Got money on my mind

15:52.886 --> 15:54.786
I can never get enough

15:54.788 --> 15:57.322
♪ And every time I step up
in the building ♪
[ Groans ]

15:57.324 --> 15:59.390
He's a child!
♪ Everybody hands go up ♪

15:59.392 --> 16:01.059
I thought you said
you were great at his.

16:01.061 --> 16:03.227
I've never played
against another person before.

16:05.332 --> 16:07.298
Told you...
no friends.

16:07.300 --> 16:08.933
♪ And they stay there ♪
Come on!

16:08.935 --> 16:10.001
♪ And they say "yeah" ♪

16:10.003 --> 16:12.270
I'm gonna beat
the black off of you.

16:12.272 --> 16:14.472
Can you
really do that?
Oh, no, sweetheart.

16:14.474 --> 16:17.075
♪ 'Cause all I do is
win, win, win ♪

16:17.077 --> 16:19.844
♪ And if you goin' in
put your hands in the air ♪
Ohh!
[ Laughs ]

16:19.846 --> 16:21.579
It's okay, Mama.
Stop it.

16:21.581 --> 16:23.748
All right, Rhonda.
I got this.
Okay.

16:23.750 --> 16:26.684
Going over the top.

16:26.686 --> 16:29.420
The anterior
Malaysian sub-grip...

16:29.422 --> 16:31.589
the Grip of Kings.

16:31.591 --> 16:34.158
Yeah, I really don't care.
I just want you to win.

16:34.160 --> 16:35.793
♪ And they stay there ♪

16:35.795 --> 16:36.761
♪ And they say "yeah" ♪

16:36.763 --> 16:37.962
♪ And they stay there ♪

16:37.964 --> 16:40.765
♪ 'Cause all I do is
win, win, win ♪

16:40.767 --> 16:43.468
♪ and if you goin' in
put your hands in the air ♪

16:43.470 --> 16:45.303
Aah! Ow!

16:45.305 --> 16:46.771
Ohh!

16:46.773 --> 16:47.972
Okay, time out.
Time out.

16:47.974 --> 16:49.607
Time... Time out?

16:49.609 --> 16:51.342
Yes.
You just hurt your wrist
playing ping-pong?

16:51.344 --> 16:53.778
It's the risk
of the sub-grip.

16:53.780 --> 16:55.313
- Do we have a forfeit?
- No!

16:55.315 --> 16:56.715
Just got to wrap this up.
He got it.

16:56.716 --> 16:58.116
I can play on this.

16:58.118 --> 17:00.284
I<i> can't</i> play on this.
Ow!

17:00.286 --> 17:02.553
Shoot me up... Steroids,
cortisone, any... Aah!

17:02.555 --> 17:03.955
Cut me, Bow.
Just cut me.

17:03.957 --> 17:05.656
Cut you?
Yes.

17:05.658 --> 17:08.393
Dre, this is a bruise at best
and a boo-boo at worst.

17:08.395 --> 17:10.194
Open your hand.
I... Ow, ow!

17:10.196 --> 17:11.662
Ohh!

17:11.664 --> 17:13.164
What is this?
Huh?

17:13.166 --> 17:14.532
This feels like
a hate-taping.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.067
Oh, God. Fine.
You know what, Dre?

17:16.069 --> 17:17.668
You're the man.
Do it yourself.

17:17.670 --> 17:19.370
I will do it myself.

17:19.372 --> 17:21.706
You don't have my name.
You don't have my back...

17:21.708 --> 17:24.809
Classic Rainbow Johnson.

17:24.811 --> 17:26.978
Yep. Yep. Okay.
What are you...

17:26.980 --> 17:30.081
Put this here.
Keep my grip.

17:30.884 --> 17:32.483
[ Grunts ]

17:32.485 --> 17:33.518
Ruby: [ Claps ]
Come on, now.

17:33.520 --> 17:36.487
Dre: Ready for this?
Five serving six.

17:36.489 --> 17:39.857
♪♪

17:39.859 --> 17:42.360
Ow!
Ohh! Aah!

17:42.362 --> 17:44.595
This must be
what childbirth feels like!

17:44.597 --> 17:45.997
Rhonda: Okay,
this is ridiculous.

17:45.999 --> 17:47.231
Dre: Aah!

17:47.233 --> 17:48.699
Look what we're doing,
everybody.

17:48.701 --> 17:49.734
This is stupid.

17:49.736 --> 17:51.269
No, no, no, no!
No, I'm cool.

17:51.271 --> 17:53.938
Sharon, listen.
I don't care what name we have.

17:53.940 --> 17:55.840
You know, for years,
we couldn't get married.

17:55.842 --> 17:57.708
But now we can.

17:57.710 --> 18:00.978
And the only name that I insist
on calling you is "wife."

18:02.449 --> 18:04.382
Sharon: That's a name
I'm happy to take.

18:04.384 --> 18:06.451
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

18:06.453 --> 18:09.387
That is so beautiful.

18:09.389 --> 18:10.455
If you guys had kissed,

18:10.457 --> 18:12.690
I would have
only<i> barely</i> turned away.

18:12.692 --> 18:13.791
[ Laughter ]

18:13.793 --> 18:15.293
Thanks, Mrs. Johnson.

18:15.295 --> 18:17.762
Oh, no more Mrs. Johnson.

18:17.764 --> 18:20.465
You call me Goodmama RuRu.

18:20.467 --> 18:22.033
[ Laughing ] Yes.

18:22.035 --> 18:23.434
Welcome to the family, baby.

18:23.436 --> 18:25.303
Oh, you two are gonna make
beautiful brides.

18:25.305 --> 18:26.971
- [ Laughs ]
- Can't wait for the wedding.

18:26.973 --> 18:29.040
You know what?
Daddy...

18:29.042 --> 18:30.708
Mm, I think
we are familied out.

18:30.710 --> 18:31.709
Elope?
What?

18:31.711 --> 18:32.610
Good idea, babe.
Yep.

18:32.612 --> 18:33.811
Junior:
So, no wedding?

18:33.813 --> 18:35.546
I was gonna go big.

18:35.548 --> 18:37.915
Uh, bigger than this?
Really?

18:37.917 --> 18:39.117
Wait, if there's no wedding,

18:39.119 --> 18:40.885
where will we do
our choreographed dance number?

18:40.887 --> 18:42.620
Diane: Hit it.

18:42.622 --> 18:45.389
[ Mary J. Blige's
"Family Affair plays ]

18:45.391 --> 18:48.126
[ Groans ] Pathetic.

18:48.128 --> 18:49.460
♪ Let's get it crunk ♪

18:49.462 --> 18:53.297
♪ we gonna have fun
up on in this dancery ♪

18:53.299 --> 18:54.632
♪ We got ya open ♪ [ Laughs ]

18:54.634 --> 18:56.134
♪ Now ya floatin' ♪ Ohh, yeah.

18:56.136 --> 18:58.603
♪ So you gots to dance for me ♪

18:58.605 --> 19:00.972
[ Laughs ] They learned that.

19:00.974 --> 19:03.741
Oh, my God, they...
[ Laughs ]
Look at that...

19:03.743 --> 19:06.010
pure desperation.

19:06.012 --> 19:08.146
♪ While you're waiting,
so just dance for me ♪

19:08.148 --> 19:09.947
[ Laughs ]

19:09.949 --> 19:12.583
Look, I just want to say
that I'm sorry

19:12.585 --> 19:14.852
for getting
so worked up over this.

19:14.854 --> 19:16.287
You should be.

19:16.289 --> 19:18.122
When we met,

19:18.124 --> 19:19.056
I was a scrub.

19:20.293 --> 19:22.093
Yes, I know.

19:22.095 --> 19:23.794
I'm serious.
Yes, I'm serious, too.

19:23.796 --> 19:25.163
And as a Black man,

19:25.165 --> 19:27.999
the odds are
already stacked against me.

19:28.001 --> 19:30.434
So, for a woman like you
to take my name

19:30.436 --> 19:31.602
when I wasn't anything...

19:31.604 --> 19:33.004
[ Family cheering ]

19:33.006 --> 19:34.926
it would've shown
that you really believed in me.

19:36.376 --> 19:39.110
And I don't need
a name change to know

19:39.112 --> 19:42.280
that you really believe
in me anymore.

19:42.282 --> 19:44.382
I fell in love
with Rainbow Johnson.

19:44.384 --> 19:47.118
Why wouldn't I want to be
married to Rainbow Johnson?

19:47.120 --> 19:48.653
Aww, Dre.

19:48.655 --> 19:51.389
Sweetheart...

19:51.391 --> 19:53.057
I love that you feel
like you can conceded

19:53.059 --> 19:54.358
something really meaningful
to me.

19:54.360 --> 19:57.995
Honestly, I don't know

19:57.997 --> 20:02.200
if I need to be
Rainbow Johnson anymore.

20:02.202 --> 20:04.969
And if you need me
to be Rainbow Johnson,

20:04.971 --> 20:06.571
I will be Rainbow Johnson.

20:06.573 --> 20:09.407
How about this?
Mm-hmm?

20:09.409 --> 20:10.808
We just stay the Johnsons?

20:10.810 --> 20:13.711
Okay, it'll take
some getting used to...
Okay.

20:13.713 --> 20:16.347
But I will give it a shot.

20:16.349 --> 20:17.748
Me, too.
I'm just... You, too?

20:17.750 --> 20:19.083
Mm-hmm.
Okay.
[ Laughs ]

20:19.085 --> 20:20.318
Oh, my God.
Come on. Mwah.

20:20.320 --> 20:22.853
Ow! [winces]
Ow!
Oh, come on, Dre.

20:22.855 --> 20:24.088
Really!
Yeah.

20:24.090 --> 20:26.390
It feels like a baby is coming
out of my wrist.

20:26.392 --> 20:27.658
You know what?
That makes sense, Dre.

20:27.660 --> 20:30.261
Because people
always say bruises,

20:30.263 --> 20:32.863
ping-pong wounds,
and birth...
Yeah, stop. Stop, stop.
Look, look...

20:32.865 --> 20:34.599
so similar,
so similar.
Okay, look
at the babies.

20:34.601 --> 20:36.434
Look at the babies dance.
Look at the babies.
[ Chuckles ]

20:36.436 --> 20:38.869
♪♪

20:38.871 --> 20:41.205
[ Cheering ]

20:41.207 --> 20:43.874
Ruby: There you go.
There you go!

20:43.876 --> 20:45.042
[ Applause, Laughter ]

20:45.044 --> 20:46.277
- [ Laughs ]
- Good job!

20:46.279 --> 20:47.799
- Yeah, guys!
- God, I love these kids.

20:52.352 --> 20:53.417
[ Poor Scottish accent ]
Aye, Donkey!

20:53.419 --> 20:54.418
[ Gasps ]
[ Normal voice ] "Shrek!"

20:54.420 --> 20:56.587
Okay.
O-Okay, um...

20:56.589 --> 20:58.456
Bill Paxton...
No, no, no, no, no.

20:58.458 --> 21:01.192
No, no, Bill<i> Pullman</i> is
the president and...

21:01.194 --> 21:03.928
and... and aliens, aliens...
[ Gasps ]

21:03.930 --> 21:04.962
"Independence Day!"

21:06.199 --> 21:08.132
You haven't seen this.
Pass!

21:10.203 --> 21:11.969
Okay, He's a wolf
on Wall Street.

21:11.971 --> 21:13.304
Yeah, he's taking
people's money.

21:13.306 --> 21:14.705
Oh...
[ Buzzer ]

21:15.908 --> 21:18.743
Oh, "Wolf of Wall Street."

21:18.745 --> 21:20.111
Should've said "Jonah Hill."
